tedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T14:55:26.000Z","msg":"No reliable source 報<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0a991e3482abcddd31587adb04b1ade26b6c7629","tid":1904374,"uid":25468,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T14:56:14.000Z","msg":"同兩個跟班一齊確診<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://mcmnt.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Pope-Francis.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmcmnt.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2FPope-Francis.jpg&h=3131d87c&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://mcmnt.com/vatican-confirms-pope-francis-and-two-aides-test-positive-for-coronavirus/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmcmnt.com%2Fvatican-confirms-pope-francis-and-two-aides-test-positive-for-coronavirus%2F&d=EEQ1dbVkwObjLGYhXKOOXBR1GjkmqS0yYYF7Sw2QOJY%3D&h=b1172628\" target=\"_blank\">https://mcmnt.com/vatican-confirms-pope-francis-and-two-aides-test-positive-for-coronavirus/</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nThe Vatican has confirmed in a statement that Pope Francis and two of his aides have tested positive for the novel Coronavirus.<br />\n<br />\nThe three new cases add up to the over 400 cases confirmed in Italy under a week.<br />\n<br />\nPope Francis missed a planned Mass with clergy in Rome yesterday after showing Coronavirus-like symptoms.<br />\n<br />\nThe Vatican had earlier said the pontiff, 83, had a slight indisposition and could proceed with the rest of his planned work today.<br />\n<br />\nThe pope and his aides have been quarantined and receiving medical attention near Santa Marta, the Vatican hotel where he lives.<br />\n<br />\nThe pope was seen coughing and blowing his nose during the Asha Wednesday Mass.<br />\n<br />\nYesterday, he told well-wishers: &lsquo;I wish, again, to express my closeness to those who are ill with coronavirus and to health-care workers who are caring for them&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\nIt comes amid an outbreak of the strain of coronavirus- also known as Covid-19 &ndash; in Italy that has infected more than 400 people, almost all of them in the north.<br />\n<br />\nRome had three cases, but all three have recovered.<br />\n<br />\nFrancis had been scheduled to go to the St John Lateran basilica to meet with Rome clergy and celebrate a penitential Mass at the start of Lent.<br />\n<br />\nThe Argentine pope has generally good health he lost part of one lung as a young man because of respiratory illness and suffers from sciatica, which makes walking difficult."},{"pid":"3f5de64430e13d580398f44732977e72511d13d7","tid":1904374,"uid":228995,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T14:56:22.000Z","msg":"Content farm"},{"pid":"88e5fe74dddae3aef611af5c062518aed9081a2a","tid":1904374,"uid":29917,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T14:58:00.000Z","msg":"教宗奶共，中都唔出奇"},{"pid":"26e03d349ed5e3fc0f0ae56af84b90e3a3f49c29","tid":1904374,"uid":203799,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T15:04:13.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c7d5ac3ce30abfa9eeef5c2854aa82c95404c315","tid":1904374,"uid":174960,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T15:07:27.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-8051083/Pope-cancels-visit-Rome-priests-slight-illness.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailymail.co.uk%2Fnews%2Farticle-8051083%2FPope-cancels-visit-Rome-priests-slight-illness.html&d=EEQ1dbVkwObjLGYhXKOOXBR1GjkmqS0yYYF7Sw2QOJY%3D&h=c972f440\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-8051083/Pope-cancels-visit-Rome-priests-slight-illness.html</a>"},{"pid":"6938138e1cc476d19c40308a6a468d9114e6d2ba","tid":1904374,"uid":263197,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T15:13:06.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://tw.appledaily.com/international/20200229/W4K6CMI2HWPO4WVR4HOANQ3QZM/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftw.appledaily.com%2Finternational%2F20200229%2FW4K6CMI2HWPO4WVR4HOANQ3QZM%2F&d=EEQ1dbVkwObjLGYhXKOOXBR1GjkmqS0yYYF7Sw2QOJY%3D&h=e0b08e04\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftw.appledaily.com%2Finternational%2F20200229%2FW4K6CMI2HWPO4WVR4HOANQ3QZM%2F&h=797ea8d5\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://tw.appledaily.com/international/20200229/W4K6CMI2HWPO4WVR4HOANQ3QZM/</a><br />\n<br />\n// 羅馬天主教教宗方濟各（Pope Francis）自周三起身體不適，連續兩天取消接見，梵蒂岡昨稱他只是「身體微恙」，引發各界關注。教宗今天（29日）已在其住所恢復正式個人接見，但取消團體接見。網路流傳一張不出名網路媒體的「教宗確診」的圖片，但未引述任何消息來源，也沒有其他媒體證實相關訊息，應屬謠言。//"},{"pid":"589ee0a86196084c751166a169c588d9da9951fa","tid":1904374,"uid":266289,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-29T15:18:40.000Z","msg":"Diu<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/superman.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"}]}